        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"694971\">Haotian Liu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/The.20set.20of.20zeros.20of.20a.20continuous.20function/near/423762940\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thank you for your answer.<br>\nIs there any theorem in Lean that can help us to prove that the zset is a closed set?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I can’t search them now, but all of the following steps should be in Mathlib: </p>\n<p>Pre-image of a continuous function g of a closed set, {0}, is closed, which are all zeros of g. The interval (Icc aleft aright) is closed. The intersection of two closed sets is closed. This is exactly your proof.</p>",
